ReviewList.Text: This book was an easy read with practical ideas. It is very organized and well written. Even if your finances are somewhat stable it's a great refresher.  I would recommend this book to anyone who handles finances.

This book is really well written with great spelling and grammar, making it a really enjoyable reading experience. The tips and strategies contained within this book are sure to aid anyone who is struggling with debt, or indeed anyone looking to stay out of debt. I really enjoyed the fact that the author went into the mindset and psychology of getting out of debt rather than just providing some financial advice. A really helpful book for anyone looking to get out of debt.

Extremely basic presentation.  The information presented in this short publication is available on the net but with much more in-depth analysis.  Anyway, for a free publication, the "Debt Free-The Ultimate Guide to Becoming.....". is readable.

It is a good book to organize your debts, gives very interesting tips so you do not waste your money and you progress economically in a short time. I really like the book, is written in a simple and complete way. Nothing is missing.
This book is well written and has some good general guidelines for breaking the debt/spend cycle.  It is short, concise, and gives useful hints for websites to make a budget and track spending
I didn't really learn anything from this book I've not already read before.  But it works well as a reinforcement of what I've learned already. So Kudos for that!
Its an okay book. Not much information that I don't already know.
